7. Sort

        Bubble sort- Core is in each iteration max element goes to right, arr[i]>arr[i+1], swap them
        Selection sort- Core is in each iteration find minimum element and swap to initial position
        Insertion sort- in each iteration we keep left array sorted and try to brin curr element to its correct position
        Merge sort- Divide and conquer. find mid, recurse from left-> , mid+1->right, merge function
        Quick sort- Pick pivot: partition such that left<pivot, right> pivot, recursively call for left->pivot-1, pivot+1>right

        | Algorithm      | Best Case      | Average Case   | Worst Case     | Space Complexity |
        | -------------- | -------------- | -------------- | -------------- | ---------------- |
        | Bubble Sort    | **O(n)**       | **O(n²)**      | **O(n²)**      | **O(1)**         |
        | Selection Sort | **O(n²)**      | **O(n²)**      | **O(n²)**      | **O(1)**         |
        | Insertion Sort | **O(n)**       | **O(n²)**      | **O(n²)**      | **O(1)**         |
        | Merge Sort     | **O(n log n)** | **O(n log n)** | **O(n log n)** | **O(n)**         |
        | Quick Sort     | **O(n log n)** | **O(n log n)** | **O(n²)**      | **O(log n)**     |


